## Code Style

<% if (isTypescript) { -%>
- Always add explicit type annotations to function parameters — never rely on implicit inference.
<% } -%>
<% if (conventions.strictTypes) { -%>
- No `any` types — use explicit types, discriminated unions, or generics.
<% } -%>
<% if (isReact) { -%>
- Use `<%= conventions.componentStyle === 'arrow' ? 'const arrow functions' : 'function declarations' %>` for all React components.
<% if (conventions.propsStyle === 'readonly') { -%>
- Wrap all component props in `Readonly<>` to prevent accidental mutation.
<% } -%>
- Extract large render blocks (>30 lines of JSX) into separate component files.
- Use `useCallback` for all event handlers passed as props to child components.
- Use `useMemo` for derived/computed values that create a new reference on every render.
<% } -%>
- Functions with more than 2 parameters must use a single object parameter.
- Name module-level constants in UPPER_SNAKE_CASE.
- Do not create thin wrapper components that only forward props.
- Avoid redundant type aliases.
- Use descriptive variable names in `.map()` callbacks.
- Avoid hardcoded styling — use theme variables or design tokens.
<% if (conventions.maxFileLength) { -%>
- Keep files under <%= conventions.maxFileLength %> lines.
<% } -%>
<% if (localeRules.length > 0) { -%>

### Locale Rules

<% localeRules.forEach(function(rule) { -%>
- <%= rule %>
<% }); -%>
<% } -%>
